25:45.175 --> 25:53.629
course, it was due to that tax money. That's what 
kept Boston so good. No doubt about that. But those

26:02.476 --> 26:12.507
people out there, they didn't get a cut until 1935 
or something when they were beginning to come out

26:02.476 --> 26:12.507
of the Depression. And they cut those people's 
salaries. But in the meantime, they kept this town

26:16.211 --> 26:20.195
going. That's interesting. You know, you 
retired, I think, at about the time that the air

26:22.458 --> 26:27.263
